Earlier this week I announced that I was co-sponsoring the Stopping Bad Robocalls Act to curb the 145 million robocalls placed every day throughout the country. I'm happy to report that the bill passed the House by a vote of 429-3. pic.twitter.com/7g5QGDFB3m
It should also call us to action. The House passed H.R. 1 and the SAFE Act to protect our democracy from foreign interference. Now it's the Senate's turn to act.

This warning from Robert Mueller — that the Russians are continually working to meddle in our elections and undermine our democracy — should concern us all, regardless of which side of the aisle we sit on.
"It wasn't a single attempt. They're doing it as we sit here." https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/24/opinion/robert-mueller-report-testimony.html …

Last night the House voted to keep my climate security legislation in the Intelligence Authorization Act (IAA). Then the IAA passed the House, 397-31.

Climate change is already causing national security threats. Let's make sure we're ready. pic.twitter.com/wTt408D0Iw

I'm proud to be a cosponsor of the #RaiseTheWage Act, which just passed the House moments ago. If enacted, this bill will result in a raise for up to 33 million American workers. pic.twitter.com/5B8NV1Bsh6

The House is getting ready to vote on the #RaiseTheWage Act. The bill:
✅gradually raises the minimum wage to $15 by 2025
✅gives up to 33 million Americans a raise, including 20 million women
✅lifts at least 1.3 million Americans out of poverty, including 600,000 children pic.twitter.com/qAjy5rBDhN

Minutes ago, the House passed my bill to designate the Tumwater Post Office for Eva G. Hewitt.

We can shore up the Affordable Care Act, increase access to care, and lower premiums. But the Trump administration is sabotaging the ACA by attacking it in court. If they succeed, millions of Americans will lose coverage -- 565,000 in Washington state alone. #ProtectOurCare pic.twitter.com/af7loXFLZ1

I try to be positive on Twitter, but the president has gone too far with the border camps. Congress is acting to implement standards of care for people in U.S. custody, but the ultimate referendum on President Trump's policies will be by the American people on November 3, 2020. pic.twitter.com/iTgz0nivIL
The situation now is heartbreaking. This is not who we are, and we must fix it.

Then we need to address the root causes of the problem at the border by fixing our immigration system, providing responsible aid to address the flow of people northward toward our border, and returning the immigration debate to one of informed and humane discourse.
